  "narrative": {
    "premise": "In the cool, drizzly late evening, a quiet trip to the familiar bookstore aisle becomes a gentle act of putting things back in order. A loose planner page, found tucked between the shelves, isn't just a scrap of paper; it's a small, misplaced piece of the day that asks to be returned, turning a simple errand into a private ritual of mending a tiny, invisible tear in the evening's fabric.",
